name: hawaii-coral-reef-assessment-and-monitoring-program-cramp-digital-still-images-from-transects-o
notes: This dataset consists of digital still images from the Hawaii Coral Reef Assessment and Monitoring Program (CRAMP) taken 2011-2012 from 29 sites within 5 main Hawaiian Islands (Kauai, Oahu, Molokai, Maui, and Hawaii). During 2011, only sites on Maui were surveyed. Most sites consist of two transects along different isobaths, shallow (~2-4m) and deep (~7-13m) lines. A total of 71 transects were completed between June 2011 - December 2012. This dataset only contains the images from which quantitative estimates of substrate type and species were acquired. The quantitative estimates in text comma-separated format are stored within a separate NODC accession, 0117490.
